## Usage

| Usage | (Number key) Shortcuts |

| 1. Set Checkpoints, Clip + VAE | (3) Checkpoint (subgraph) |
| 2. (optional) add LoRAs | (1) Settings, Prompt, Image, Video |
| 3. Enable Featuras you want with the "Features - Switch" | (1) Settings, Prompt, Image, Video |

| 5. Add image you need + Audio file | |
| 6. Write your prompts | |
| 7. Generate | |
|Optional: Tune any internal setting | (2) Backend (subgraph) |

nodes.title: Resolution note
widgets_values:
### Automatic scaling and resolution calculation The initial image will be scaled on optimized math targeting a WAN 2.2 VAE (div16) resolution. Aspect will be calculated automatically and the video resolution will be set to the nearest possible match with the megapixel count. | Stage | Target MP | Quality | Use case | |---:|---:|---:|---| | 1 | 0.25 | Preview
~ 360p| Motion/physics tests. | | 2 | 0.33 | Fast
~ 432p| Simple quality. | | 3 | 0.40 | SD Speed
~ 480p| "Sweet spot" for speed. | | 4 | 0.60 | SD
~ 576p| Optimal for mobile-first content. | | 5 | 0.72 | Balanced HD
~ 640p| Consistent, good details. | | 6 | 0.85 | HD
~ 720p| Very stable, crisp details. | | 7 | 1.05 | THD
~ 768p| Maximum stability for Image-to-Video. | | 8 | 1.15 | THD+
~ 800p| 16GB VRAM "sweet spot". | | 9 | 1.30 | HQ
~ 900p| High detail, very slow (Requires high VRAM). | | 10 | 2.07 | FHD
~ 1080p| Production grade detail, extreme slow (Requires very high VRAM). |

nodes.title: Features
widgets_values:
| Feature | Default / Example | Description | |--------:|------------------:|------------:| | **NAG** | off | This will use your negative condition and concat it with the standard WAN AI negative prompt for convenience.
If you do not want this, just disable the standard negative node.
‚ö†Ô∏èNAG needs a lot of VRAM, so if you do not need this. Just let it be disabled. | | **Extend** | off | Set extra batches and enable the "Extend" feature, this will extent the video the amount of extra rounds with your set frames. Possibly expanding it infinitely. Set the extra batches and frames per batch to the desired audio length.
(Example: 15s audio = 81 frames with 2 extra batches) | | **Interpolation** | off | This will interpolate your video to double fps at the end. Interpolated FPS = 2 √ó FPS. | | **Upscale** | off | Final resolution = 2 √ó start resolution while maintaining aspect ratio. No morph; aspect-correct to optimal WAN resolution. | | **Soundmark** | off | Enable for a soundmark overlay on video. | | **Watermark** | off | Enable for a watermark overlay on video. | | **Color match** | off | This will try to match the color from the initial image to the samples. The color match algorithms default is set by default to '0.5'. Feel free to test other strength. |

nodes.title: BASIC settings
widgets_values:
| Setting | Default / Example | Description | |--------:|------------------:|------------:| | **Seconds** | 5 | Set the desired length of the video in seconds. | | **CRF** | 20, webm, VP9 | Video compression level. Visually lossless. Set on VHS Node.| | **FPS** | 16 | Frames per second for videos. Use 24 for faster motion/shorter videos. | | **Shift** | 5 | Default 5. Adjust and test; WAN 2.2 valid in range 5‚Äì8. | | **Steps total** | 4 | Total steps - node handles step math. More steps ‚Üí higher quality but longer generation. Use even numbers. | | **CFG** | 1.0 | Controls prompt adherence. Use 1-1.5. 1 disables/ignores the negative prompt. 1.0 is needed for speed-up's like 4/8-step models/LoRAs | | **Extra batches** | 1 | Controls how much extra loops for extending the video will be added. See "Extend"-feature. | | **Sampler** | euler | "Euler" works everytime. Other samplers can enhance detail or motion. This has major impact on how the video is generated. | | **Scheduler** | simple | "Simple" works eveytime. Other like "beta" and others can enhance some samplers. | | **Seed** | number + randomize | Random outcome every run. Set a specific seed to reproduce the same outcome. | | **Sage Attention** | disabled | Can be enabled **if installed correctly** to speed-up video generation times. | | **Watermark upload** | none | Here you can upload a watermark image and calibrate the settings to your liking (subgraph). | | **Soundmark upload** | none | Here you can upload a soundmark image and calibrate the settings to your liking (subgraph). | | **Positive prompt** | none | Write your positive prompt!
1) Brief description of the setting/appearance
2) Actions, motions, story
3) Camera composition
CFG 1 normally disables/ignores the negative prompt! NAG effectively enables negative prompting on CFG 1.| | **Negative prompt** | none | Write what you would like to exclude. Works only if CFG > 1 or NAG is enabled | | **Checkpoints** | Safetensors/GGUf |Choose the type of Checkpoint to use. Wan 2.2 S2V uses a single checkpoint. You can ether use safetensors or gguf.| | **CLIP** | standard encoder | Use your preferred standard CLIP text encoder. No CLIP Vision H ‚Äî not trained/implemented in WAN 2.2 and weights are disabled. | | **VAE** | same as WAN 2.1 | Still using the same VAE as WAN 2.1. |
